SENATE RESOLUTION 397
By Seal
A RESOLUTION to commend Amaya Garrett for exemplary
service as a legislative intern.
WHEREAS, each legislative session, we are pleased to recognize certain persons who
have committed themselves, through their adroit service, to the betterment of the legislative
process; and
WHEREAS, Amaya Garrett is one such individual, who has distinguished herself in her
role as a legislative intern for Senator Jessie Seal; Ms. Garrett's work has resulted in
innumerable benefits for the legislators she assisted and the General Assembly as a whole; and
WHEREAS, a senior at Tennessee State University, where she is highly regarded by her
peers, Ms. Garrett has achieved academic success while majoring in political science with a
minor in English; and
WHEREAS, as a member of Phi Alpha Delta, Ms. Garrett participates in service and law-
related initiatives while also supporting inclusion and community engagement efforts; and
WHEREAS, Amaya Garrett is also an active member of the National Society of
Leadership and Success, where she develops her leadership skills via service activities and
collaborates with peers to foster personal and professional growth; and
WHEREAS, she is additionally involved with the Blue Ink Literary Journal, promoting
student submissions and assisting with flyer designs and public engagement; and
WHEREAS, Ms. Garrett is dedicated to serving her community via volunteer work; she
supports Project C.U.R.E. by organizing and preparing medical supplies for distribution and
assists with meals, shelter services, and community programs for the Nashville Rescue Mission;
and
SR0397
017258
- 1 -

WHEREAS, eager to familiarize herself with the characteristics and complexities of
Tennessee State government and to further her studies, Ms. Garrett brought her many abilities
and singular expertise to Capitol Hill for the 2026 session of the One Hundred Fourteenth
General Assembly; and
WHEREAS, throughout the 2026 legislative session, Amaya Garrett has surpassed all
criteria that define a devoted and conscientious legislative intern; and
WHEREAS, Ms. Garrett has performed her many duties with extraordinary insight and
rare decorum; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF THE ONE HUNDRED FOURTEENTH
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, that we hereby commend Amaya
Garrett for outstanding service as a legislative intern for Senator Jessie Seal and extend to her
our best wishes for every future success.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy.
